05:40.296 --> 05:43.212
ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, BREATHE.

05:44.256 --> 05:46.998
ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, BREATHE.

05:49.000 --> 05:50.480
ALRIGHT, SO THAT'S ABOUT IT CARTER.

05:50.611 --> 05:52.787
YOU JUST PUMP ON
THE VICTIM'S CHEST RHYTHMICALLY

05:52.917 --> 05:54.615
AND BREATHE INTO THEIR MOUTH.

05:54.745 --> 05:56.617
HOBIE, CAN I HAVE MY DOG BACK NOW?

05:56.747 --> 05:58.140
SURE, ASHLEY.

05:59.271 --> 06:00.534
THANK YOU, MUFFIN.

06:01.535 --> 06:03.014
COME ON, MUFFY.

06:04.320 --> 06:06.366
SO, YOU GET THE MAIN IDEA, RIGHT?

06:10.500 --> 06:13.460
HEY ASHLEY, DON'T TAKE THAT RAFT
IN THE WATER OKAY?

06:17.681 --> 06:20.031
HEY, THIS IS CARTER. HE JUST MOVED HERE.

06:21.511 --> 06:23.557
MAN, YOU'RE JUST IN TIME FOR
THE JUNIOR GUARD COMPETITION.

06:23.687 --> 06:25.297
REALLY? THAT'S GREAT.

06:25.428 --> 06:27.082
IT'S GONNA BE COOL,
IT'S A FATHER/SON COMPETITION.

06:28.953 --> 06:30.346
MY DAD'S GONNA CREAM ALL YOUR DADS.

06:30.477 --> 06:31.695
YEAH, RIGHT.

06:32.914 --> 06:34.611
WHAT IF MY DAD CAN'T BE IN IT?

06:34.742 --> 06:36.308
WHAT'S THE MATTER, YOUR DAD
OUT OF SHAPE OR SOMETHING?

06:36.439 --> 06:39.355
NO, HE'S AN AWESOME ATHLETE,
BUT I JUST REMEMBERED,

06:39.921 --> 06:42.271
HE'S IN THIS REALLY BIG TENNIS TOURNAMENT
THIS WEEKEND.

06:42.880 --> 06:44.055
HE'S ALWAYS IN SOME SORT OF TOURNAMENT.

06:44.186 --> 06:45.274
[WHISTLE]

06:45.405 --> 06:46.928
LET'S MOVE IT GUYS!

06:47.058 --> 06:48.712
IF YOU WANNA GET IN SHAPE
FOR THIS COMPETITION

06:48.843 --> 06:49.670
WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO WORK.

06:50.366 --> 06:51.585
LET'S GO! BUOY SWIM.

07:01.595 --> 07:03.945
HEY, WE GOTTA GO!

07:04.075 --> 07:05.555
NO, NO, NO.

07:05.686 --> 07:06.817
I NEVER WANNA GET OUT.
THIS FEELS WAY TOO GOOD.

07:06.948 --> 07:08.123
WELL COME ON, THE SOONER WE GET OUT,

07:08.253 --> 07:09.907
THE SOONER WE FIND OUR BEACH ASSIGNMENTS.

07:10.038 --> 07:11.169
AND ROOKIE OF THE YEAR.

07:11.866 --> 07:13.345
AND WHO GETS TO PICK WHAT BEACH.

07:20.222 --> 07:23.747
WELL, LOGAN CAME IN FIRST
SO LOGAN IS ROOKIE OF THE YEAR,

07:23.878 --> 07:25.227
SO HE'S GONNA GET TO PICK
WHAT BEACH HE WANTS.

07:25.923 --> 07:28.099
I JUST KNOW ,HE'S GONNA PICK
BAYWATCH AND IF HE DOES

07:28.230 --> 07:30.450
I DON'T KNOW WHAT I'M GONNA DO
BECAUSE I CANNOT WORK WITH HIM.

07:30.580 --> 07:32.060
IT'LL BE A COMPLETE DISASTER.

07:32.887 --> 07:34.889
WELL ALL I KNOW IS THAT
IF I'M ASSIGNED BAYWATCH,

07:35.019 --> 07:36.804
I'M GONNA REQUEST ANOTHER BEACH.

07:36.934 --> 07:38.588
LISTEN, HE'S GONNA PICK MALIBU
BECAUSE THAT'S WHERE HIS...

07:43.288 --> 07:44.986
EVERYBODY WANTS MALIBU.

07:45.116 --> 07:47.249
YOU MEAN THAT'S WHERE SHE LIVES.

07:47.858 --> 07:49.469
YOU KNOW WHAT, IT DOESN'T
MATTER ANYWAY BECAUSE

07:49.599 --> 07:51.558
I'M NOT WORKING WITH HIM
AND THAT'S ALL THERE IS TO IT.

07:51.688 --> 07:54.865
OH CAROLINE, I KNOW HOW AWKWARD
THIS IS FOR YOU,

07:55.518 --> 07:57.128
BUT YOU JUST CAN'T LET LOGAN HAVE

07:57.259 --> 07:58.652
THIS KIND OF POWER OVER YOUR LIFE.

07:58.782 --> 08:01.089
I SAY LET'S NOT BORROW TROUBLE.

08:01.219 --> 08:02.525
THERE'S A LOT OF GREAT BEACHES,

08:02.656 --> 08:03.744
HE'S PROBABLY NOT EVEN GONNA PICK
BAYWATCH.

08:04.396 --> 08:05.833
MAYBE I WON'T EVEN GET BAYWATCH.

08:06.573 --> 08:08.226
LOUDSPEAKER: ALL LIFEGUARDS REPORT TO THE DECK

08:08.357 --> 08:10.490
IN 15 MINUTES FOR BEACH ASSIGNMENTS.

08:10.620 --> 08:12.535
WELL, I GUESS WE'LL FIND OUT SOON ENOUGH.

08:14.276 --> 08:15.799
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT,
ALRIGHT I WON'T KEEP YOU

08:15.930 --> 08:17.845
IN SUSPENSE ANY LONGER.
THE BEACH ASSIGNMENTS ARE...

08:17.975 --> 08:20.935
MALIBU: BATES, CONNOR, WADE.

08:21.065 --> 08:25.374
-[CHEERING]
-[APPLAUSE]

08:25.505 --> 08:28.203
SANTA MONICA: MARTIN AND MR. TOMMY MOORE.

08:29.378 --> 08:31.511
VENICE: SAMPLES AND CLARK.

08:34.688 --> 08:38.169
AND RIGHT HERE AT BAYWATCH:
HOLDEN AND BERNARD.

08:38.299 --> 08:39.693
-[APPLAUSE]

08:42.173 --> 08:45.046
SEE? I TOLD YOU YOUR SISTER
WOULD BE SURE YOU GOT BAYWATCH.

08:47.309 --> 08:48.702
MITCH: NOW IF I COULD HAVE
EVERYONE'S ATTENTION.

08:48.832 --> 08:50.399
AS YOU KNOW, THE ROOKIE
OF THE YEAR IS ENTITLED

08:50.530 --> 08:52.444
TO CHOOSE HIS OR HER BEACH ASSIGNMENT.

08:52.575 --> 08:55.273
THIS YEAR, OUR ROOKIE
OF THE YEAR AWARD GOES TO

08:56.100 --> 08:59.800
OUR EXCHANGE LIFEGUARD
FROM AUSTRALIA, LOGAN FOWLER.

08:59.930 --> 09:03.064
[APPLAUSE]

09:05.806 --> 09:08.243
HE'S NOT A ROOKIE.
HE'S BEEN A LIFEGUARD FOR YEARS.

09:08.373 --> 09:09.897
WELL, THERE'S NOTHING WE CAN DO ABOUT IT

09:10.027 --> 09:12.900
SO DON'T GIVE HIM THE SATISFACTION.
JUST SMILE.

09:13.553 --> 09:15.163
MITCH: CONGRATULATIONS.

09:15.293 --> 09:17.557
NOW, THE CHOICE OF THE BEACH IS YOURS.

09:17.687 --> 09:19.341
OKAY.

09:19.471 --> 09:22.649
WELL I'VE GIVEN IT A LOT OF THOUGHT,
AND AFTER EVERYTHING

09:22.779 --> 09:24.694
I'VE BEEN THROUGH WITH EVERYBODY,

09:24.825 --> 09:26.435
WITH THE EARTHQUAKE AND ALL,

09:26.566 --> 09:28.350
I FEEL THAT THIS IS WHERE I BELONG.

09:30.613 --> 09:31.658
I CHOOSE BAYWATCH.

09:31.788 --> 09:34.182
-[CHEERING]
-[APPLAUSE]

09:45.062 --> 09:47.456
OKAY, THAT WAS A GREAT PRACTICE,

09:47.587 --> 09:49.240
BUT IN THE REAL COMPETITION,

09:49.371 --> 09:51.416
YOUR DADS WILL HIT THE WATER NEXT.

09:51.547 --> 09:54.245
SO YOU JUNIOR GUARDS,
DOESN'T MATTER WHERE YOU PLACE,

09:54.376 --> 09:56.944
IT'S YOUR DADS WHO ARE GONNA MAKE IT
OR BREAK IT FOR YA.

09:57.858 --> 09:59.381
NEXT IS THE RUNNING RELAY,
SO WHAT YOU HAVE TO DO

09:59.511 --> 10:01.862
IS TO DECIDE WHO IS THE BEST SWIMMER

10:01.992 --> 10:04.299
AND WHO IS THE BEST RUNNER,
THE FATHER OR THE SON.

10:05.039 --> 10:06.780
OKAY GUYS, LET'S GET READY
FOR THE NEXT HEAT.

10:06.910 --> 10:09.347
READY? ALL RIGHT, LET'S HAVE FUN.

10:09.478 --> 10:10.435
KID: LOOK, THERE'S A DWARF.

10:10.566 --> 10:11.741
THINK HE'S GOT ENOUGH STUFF?

10:25.407 --> 10:26.408
ALL RIGHT.

10:32.327 --> 10:34.503
KID: LOOK AT HIM. HE MUST BE LOST.

10:35.112 --> 10:36.244
I'LL GO TALK TO HIM.

10:36.374 --> 10:37.898
SEE IF HE NEEDS DIRECTIONS OR SOMETHING.

10:38.028 --> 10:38.899
OKAY.

10:46.907 --> 10:48.299
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE, SIMON?

10:48.430 --> 10:50.737
I GOT A CALL AT MY OFFICE ABOUT PRACTICE

10:50.867 --> 10:51.868
FOR THE FATHER/SON COMPETITION.

10:54.436 --> 10:55.567
I LEFT RIGHT AWAY.

10:56.177 --> 10:57.395
YOU DIDN'T HAVE TO COME.

10:57.526 --> 10:58.527
I WANTED TO BE HERE FOR YOU, SON.

10:58.658 --> 10:59.963
SORRY I'M LATE.

11:00.094 --> 11:01.312
COME ON, LET'S JOIN THE OTHERS.

11:01.443 --> 11:05.926
NO. I MEAN, I DON'T FEEL GOOD.

11:06.056 --> 11:08.145
I GOTTA USE THE BATHROOM.

11:08.972 --> 11:10.191
CARTER?

11:11.932 --> 11:12.933
CARTER!

11:13.934 --> 11:14.761
CARTER!

11:24.901 --> 11:26.773
OKAY GUYS, COME ON WITH ME.
WE'LL GET YOU GOING.

11:26.903 --> 11:27.904
COME ON.

11:29.427 --> 11:30.777
CAN I GIVE YOU A HAND WITH THAT?

11:31.473 --> 11:32.909
THANKS.

11:33.040 --> 11:35.042
BUT WHAT I REALLY NEED
IS TO GET TO MY SON.

11:38.828 --> 11:40.787
HI, MY NAME'S MATT BRODY.

11:42.179 --> 11:44.138
SIMON MCKAY, CARTER'S FATHER.

11:44.704 --> 11:47.663
[SOMBER MUSIC]

11:57.760 --> 12:00.458
HEY, YOU OKAY?

12:02.025 --> 12:03.070
I GUESS.

12:04.724 --> 12:05.812
YOUR DAD'S LOOKING FOR YOU.

12:06.856 --> 12:07.901
YOU MEAN SIMON?

12:09.206 --> 12:10.468
HE IS YOUR DAD, ISN'T HE?

12:14.864 --> 12:18.259
MY MOM DIED LAST YEAR,
SO I CAME OUT HERE TO LIVE WITH SIMON.

12:19.042 --> 12:20.652
MY AUNT TOLD ME HE WAS MY DAD.

12:22.219 --> 12:23.743
BUT HOW COULD HE BE MY DAD?

12:23.873 --> 12:25.266
MY MOM WAS ALWAYS TELLING ME

12:25.396 --> 12:27.181
MY DAD WAS THIS GREAT ATHLETE AND ALL.

12:29.052 --> 12:30.445
BUT WHEN I MET SIMON...

12:30.575 --> 12:32.447
HE WASN'T THE FANTASY DAD

12:32.577 --> 12:34.275
THAT YOU HAD PICTURED ALL THOSE YEARS.

12:36.103 --> 12:37.669
AND THAT'S WHY YOU LIED ABOUT HIM.

12:37.800 --> 12:39.846
AND THAT'S WHY YOU RAN AWAY
FROM HIM TODAY.

12:40.672 --> 12:42.587
I JUST DIDN'T WANT PEOPLE TO KNOW THAT...

12:43.545 --> 12:44.676
THAT HE'S MY DAD.

12:47.636 --> 12:50.160
JUST BECAUSE HE LOOKS A CERTAIN WAY?

12:52.467 --> 12:54.904
ALL THESE PEOPLE OUT HERE
ARE SO PERFECT LOOKING

12:55.035 --> 12:57.515
AND LOOKS SEEM SO IMPORTANT TO EVERYBODY.

12:57.646 --> 12:58.734
SEEMS LIKE YOU HAVE TO LOOK

12:58.865 --> 13:00.127
A CERTAIN WAY JUST TO MAKE FRIENDS.

13:00.997 --> 13:02.912
I KNOW HOW IMPORTANT IT IS FOR YOU

13:03.043 --> 13:06.133
TO FIT IN AND MAKE FRIENDS,
BUT I DON'T THINK

13:06.263 --> 13:08.135
YOU'RE GIVING YOUR DAD
A FAIR CHANCE TO BE YOUR DAD.

13:09.136 --> 13:11.573
I ALWAYS THOUGHT MY DAD
WOULD BE SOMEONE LIKE YOU.

13:14.532 --> 13:15.925
WHY CAN'T YOU HAVE BEEN MY DAD?

13:17.361 --> 13:19.537
WHY DID MY DAD HAVE TO BE A DWARF?

13:24.455 --> 13:25.630
CARTER...

13:28.068 --> 13:30.461
THE ONLY THING A MAN SHOULD BE MEASURED BY

13:31.593 --> 13:32.812
IS THE SIZE OF HIS HEART.

13:36.816 --> 13:37.729
COME ON.

13:37.860 --> 13:40.732
[SOMBER MUSIC]

14:13.548 --> 14:15.811
I HOPE THIS MEANS WHAT I THINK IT DOES.

14:15.942 --> 14:17.900
SISTER DEAR WHEN YOU
ARE RIGHT YOU ARE RIGHT.

14:18.031 --> 14:20.207
THERE IS NO WAY I'M GONNA LET LOGAN FOWLER

14:20.337 --> 14:22.122
GET IN THE WAY OF SOMETHING THAT I WANT.

14:22.252 --> 14:23.340
ALL RIGHT.

14:28.171 --> 14:31.087
YEAH, LOGAN FOWLER IS DEFINITELY
OUT OF MY SYSTEM.

14:45.841 --> 14:46.886
GREAT DAY.

14:47.016 --> 14:48.235
LOOKS LIKE IT'S GONNA BE PRETTY HOT

14:48.365 --> 14:49.410
SO WEAR LOTS OF SUNBLOCK, OKAY?

15:08.081 --> 15:09.256
STEPHANIE: HOW'S IT GOING?

15:10.866 --> 15:11.867
GOING GREAT.

15:11.998 --> 15:13.956
GOOD, I'M GONNA PATROL DOWN SOUTH.

15:14.087 --> 15:15.305
KEEP AN EYE ON THAT LITTLE GIRL.

15:15.436 --> 15:16.785
HER MOTHER LOOKS LIKE SHE'S SLEEPING.

15:16.916 --> 15:17.829
ALL RIGHT.

15:17.960 --> 15:18.918
ALL RIGHT, SEE YOU LATER.

15:43.203 --> 15:44.508
WELL, THANK YOU.

15:44.639 --> 15:45.857
I LOOK FORWARD TO IT.

15:53.213 --> 15:54.301
NOW, YOU TWO HAVE A GOOD DAY.

15:59.828 --> 16:01.090
YOU KNOW THE 20 SECOND RULE.

16:01.221 --> 16:02.918
YOU WERE DEFINITELY TALKING TO THOSE GIRLS

16:03.049 --> 16:03.875
FOR MORE THAN 20 SECONDS.

16:04.006 --> 16:05.616
YEAH, I KNOW THE RULE.

16:06.487 --> 16:08.097
I JUST DIDN'T THINK YOU HAD ME
ON THE CLOCK.

16:08.228 --> 16:09.446
WELL, NOW YOU KNOW.

16:20.109 --> 16:20.980
HELP!

16:23.983 --> 16:25.854
HELP! HELP!

16:32.556 --> 16:35.951
CAROLINE! I NEED BACKUP!

16:37.909 --> 16:40.521
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

16:56.232 --> 16:58.582
LOGAN, WATCH OUR WATER!

17:50.286 --> 17:51.896
MA'AM PLEASE, LET US DO OUR JOB, OKAY?

17:52.027 --> 17:53.028
WE'LL TAKE CARE OF HER.

17:54.508 --> 17:55.944
NO PULSE.

17:57.293 --> 18:00.862
ONE AND TWO AND THREE AND FOUR AND FIVE.

18:00.992 --> 18:04.779
ONE AND TWO AND THREE AND FOUR AND FIVE.

18:05.867 --> 18:07.956
ONE AND TWO AND THREE AND FOUR AND...

18:08.087 --> 18:10.480
[COUGHING]

18:10.611 --> 18:11.525
SWEETIE.

18:11.655 --> 18:13.266
OH, THANK GOD!

18:14.005 --> 18:15.181
ARE YOU OKAY?

18:31.066 --> 18:32.894
LANCE, WILL YOU TAKE THESE PEOPLE
BACK TO HEADQUARTERS

18:33.024 --> 18:33.982
AND MAKE SURE THEY'RE OKAY?

18:35.418 --> 18:36.941
CJ, WILL YOU WATCH MY WATER?

18:40.206 --> 18:41.946
CJ: WE'RE GONNA TAKE YOU BACK
TO HEADQUARTERS NOW.

18:54.742 --> 18:56.265
CAROLINE, WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU?

18:56.396 --> 18:58.354
I SPECIFICALLY TOLD YOU
TO WATCH THAT LITTLE GIRL.

18:58.485 --> 18:59.964
SHE WAS RIGHT IN FRONT OF YOU.

19:01.314 --> 19:03.098
DON'T YOU THINK I FEEL GUILTY ENOUGH
AS IT IS?

19:03.229 --> 19:04.795
CAROLINE, YOU'RE A LIFEGUARD.

19:04.926 --> 19:06.493
I EXPECT YOU TO FEEL GUILTY
WHEN YOU MISS A RESCUE.

19:06.623 --> 19:08.190
STEPHANIE I TOLD YOU
IT WOULD BE A DISASTER

19:08.321 --> 19:10.453
IF LOGAN AND I WORKED ON THE SAME BEACH.

19:10.584 --> 19:11.715
LOOK WHAT HAPPENED.

19:11.846 --> 19:12.803
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?

19:13.543 --> 19:15.589
I DON'T SEE WHY I HAVE TO SPELL
THIS OUT FOR YOU.

19:16.764 --> 19:18.331
I WAS WATCHING LOGAN.

19:19.070 --> 19:20.333
THAT'S WHY I MISSED THE RESCUE.

19:35.174 --> 19:36.697
CJ SAID YOU WANTED TO SEE ME.

19:37.263 --> 19:38.394
WHAT CAN I DO FOR YOU?

19:40.788 --> 19:42.703
WELL FOR STARTERS,
YOU CAN GET OFF MY PAPERWORK.

19:43.356 --> 19:44.444
OH.

19:47.229 --> 19:48.970
WE'RE OVERSTAFFED HERE AT BAYWATCH,

19:49.100 --> 19:51.015
SO I'LL BE TRANSFERRING YOU TO ZUMA
AT THE END OF THE WEEK.

19:51.146 --> 19:52.626
THEY NEED YOU, YOU'LL LIKE IT THERE.

19:52.756 --> 19:54.323
WAIT A MINUTE.

19:54.454 --> 19:57.587
I GET MY CHOICE OF BEACH,
AND I CHOSE BAYWATCH.

19:57.718 --> 19:58.893
YOU CAN'T FIRE ME.

19:59.850 --> 20:01.722
I'M NOT FIRING YOU,
I'M JUST REASSIGNING YOU.

20:01.852 --> 20:02.984
WHY?

20:07.945 --> 20:09.730
YOU'RE GETTING RID OF ME
BECAUSE OF YOUR SISTER, AREN'T YOU?

20:09.860 --> 20:11.384
OH, THAT'S RIDICULOUS.

20:11.514 --> 20:13.124
IS IT, LIEUTENANT?

20:15.388 --> 20:17.477
YOUR SISTER MISSES A RESCUE
AND I GET TRANSFERRED

20:17.607 --> 20:18.739
FOR BREAKING UP WITH HER?

20:21.568 --> 20:23.178
WEL,L YOU WON'T GET AWAY WITH IT.

20:51.946 --> 20:54.078
CAROLINE, WHAT'S WRONG NOW?

20:55.254 --> 20:57.473
YOU, STEPHANIE. YOU'RE WHAT'S WRONG.

20:59.301 --> 21:00.607
OH, WELL DON'T TELL ME
YOU HAVE NOTHING TO SAY.

21:00.737 --> 21:01.869
THAT'S A HUGE SWITCH.

21:01.999 --> 21:03.218
CAROLINE, IF I'VE DONE SOMETHING...

21:03.349 --> 21:06.134
YES YOU HAVE DONE SOMETHING, STEPHANIE.

21:06.265 --> 21:07.918
LOOK, I DON'T NEED YOU STICKING UP FOR ME

21:08.049 --> 21:09.137
AND I DON'T NEED YOU TRANSFERRING LOGAN

21:09.268 --> 21:10.660
TO ANOTHER BEACH FOR MY SAKE.

21:11.226 --> 21:12.662
I CAN HANDLE MY OWN PROBLEMS.

21:14.011 --> 21:15.317
BUT CAROLINE, YOU TOLD ME YOU COULDN'T

21:15.448 --> 21:16.753
HANDLE WORKING WITH LOGAN.

21:16.884 --> 21:18.494
YEAH, BUT I DID NOT ASK YOU TO INTERFERE.

21:19.190 --> 21:20.888
LOOK STEPHANIE,
I NEED TO BE ABLE TO TALK TO YOU

21:21.018 --> 21:22.237
WITHOUT FEELING LIKE YOU'RE ALWAYS

21:22.368 --> 21:23.586
GONNA HAVE TO COME TO MY RESCUE.

21:23.717 --> 21:25.588
LET ME SINK OR SWIM ON MY OWN.

21:27.155 --> 21:28.287
WELL CAROLINE, YOU LET SOMEONE

21:28.417 --> 21:29.940
ALMOST SINK OUT THERE YESTERDAY.

21:30.071 --> 21:31.768
I SUPPOSE YOU EXPECT ME
TO IGNORE THAT TOO.

21:33.248 --> 21:36.773
I MISSED A RESCUE STEPHANIE,
I SCREWED UP, ALL RIGHT?

21:36.904 --> 21:38.732
I FEEL BAD ENOUGH.

21:38.862 --> 21:40.821
WELL, YOU SCREWED UP BECAUSE YOU WERE
BEING DISTRACTED BY LOGAN.

21:40.951 --> 21:42.736
-NEED A REFEREE?
-BOTH: NO!

21:42.866 --> 21:44.303
LOOK, I'M GONNA GO TO WORK.

21:50.918 --> 21:52.311
WOW.

21:52.441 --> 21:53.964
GOD, I WISH SHE'D STOP
TRYING TO BE MY MOTHER.

21:54.095 --> 21:55.488
WELL STEPHANIE'S YOUR BIG SISTER,

21:55.618 --> 21:57.141
SHE JUST FEELS PROTECTIVE.

21:57.272 --> 21:58.926
WHAT'S REALLY BOTHERING YOU?

21:59.056 --> 22:00.536
I JUST CAN'T BELIEVE THAT I LET GO

22:00.667 --> 22:02.451
OF A GREAT GUY LIKE MATT FOR LOGAN.

22:04.061 --> 22:07.326
-OH CJ I'M SORRY, I...
-THAT'S OKAY.

22:08.892 --> 22:11.460
IT'S JUST THE THING IS, IS LOGAN DUMPS ME

22:11.591 --> 22:12.983
AND I'M STILL INCREDIBLY ATTRACTED TO HIM.

22:13.114 --> 22:14.333
I MEAN, I DON'T GET IT.

22:15.290 --> 22:16.378
WELL, WHEN I FIGURE THAT ONE OUT,

22:16.509 --> 22:17.858
I'M GONNA WRITE A BEST-SELLER.

22:18.772 --> 22:19.903
MEN.

22:30.914 --> 22:32.263
DOLLAR FOR YOUR THOUGHTS?

22:33.700 --> 22:34.744
THAT'S SOME INFLATION.

22:35.658 --> 22:37.094
AND THAT WAS SOME DECISION YOU MADE

22:37.225 --> 22:38.269
WITHOUT CONSULTING ME.

22:39.053 --> 22:42.056
OH, DON'T TELL ME, LOGAN CAME TO SEE YOU.

22:42.186 --> 22:44.232
TELL ME YOU HAVE A LEGITIMATE, FAIR REASON

22:44.363 --> 22:46.974
FOR TRANSFERRING HIM
AND I'M BEHIND YOU 100 PERCENT.

22:47.104 --> 22:49.193
BUT, IF YOU'RE TRANSFERRING HIM

22:49.324 --> 22:50.804
BECAUSE OF HIS RELATIONSHIP
WITH CAROLINE...

22:50.934 --> 22:52.806
LOOK MITCH, SHE WAS JUST SO SAD, YOU KNOW?

22:52.936 --> 22:54.590
I WAS TRYING TO HELP.

22:54.721 --> 22:56.244
THEN CAROLINE IS THE REASON
YOU'RE TRANSFERRING HIM.

22:57.201 --> 22:59.726
STEPHANIE, LOGAN MADE IT VERY CLEAR
THAT IF HE'S TRANSFERRED

22:59.856 --> 23:01.858
FROM BAYWATCH,
HE'LL SUE FOR DISCRIMINATION.

23:01.989 --> 23:04.034
HE'LL SUE AND HE'LL WIN, YOU KNOW THAT.

23:04.644 --> 23:06.733
HE'S GOT EVERY RIGHT TO BE EVALUATED
AS A LIFEGUARD,

23:06.863 --> 23:08.212
NOT AS AN EX-BOYFRIEND.

23:09.344 --> 23:10.867
HE'S NOT THE ONE WHO MISSED THE RESCUE.

23:10.998 --> 23:12.521
I KNOW, I KNOW.

23:13.479 --> 23:15.916
OKAY MITCH, I WAS WRONG

23:16.046 --> 23:18.092
AND I WILL TAKE RESPONSIBILITY FOR THAT.

23:19.310 --> 23:21.225
I GUESS CAROLINE WILL JUST HAVE
TO FIND A WAY

23:21.356 --> 23:22.923
TO WORK WITH LOGAN PROFESSIONALLY.

23:24.315 --> 23:25.795
WE FOUND A WAY TO WORK TOGETHER

23:25.926 --> 23:27.318
AFTER WE BROKE UP, DIDN'T WE?

23:27.449 --> 23:30.321
YEAH, BUT IT WAS A PRETTY ROUGH ROAD.

23:30.452 --> 23:31.627
I MEAN YOU ALMOST TRANSFERRED ME.

23:31.758 --> 23:32.802
BUT I DIDN'T.

23:32.933 --> 23:34.891
AND WE BECAME VERY GOOD FRIENDS.

23:35.022 --> 23:36.284
WE DID, DIDN'T WE?

23:39.635 --> 23:43.726
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

